HEADWORD: Coticular
<hw>Co*tic"u*lar</hw> <pr>(k?-t?k"?-l?r)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>coticula</ets> a small touchstone, dim. <ets>cos</ets>,
<ets>cotis</ets>, whetstone.]</ety> <def>Pertaining to whetstones; like
or suitable for whetstones.</def>⟦br⟧
